- 'Shining star in the crowd' refers to the most popular or highly rated publication;
- 'Cumulative score' is a weighted sum of the average rating, views in the last month, and downloads in the last week, with weights 0.4, 0.3, and 0.3 respectively;
- 'Stands out' implies the publication with the highest cumulative score.

sql:
SELECT COALESCE(SUM(T2.views), 0) AS total_views
FROM publications T1
LEFT JOIN statistics T2 ON T1.publication_id = T2.publication_id;
